                           •
                        , as amáre, amáte, dovère, dovéte, leggére, leggète, sentire, sentite, facete, and dicete, are not to be vſed, sete, you be, or are, is of the Verbe èſsere, to be, of the which wee will ſpeake hereafter.
                  The thirde in all Verbes may looſe, and leaue the laſt vowell, ſaying, aman, veggon, leggon, di
